types.description:
Response payload for admin-specific operations.

## Fields
- `success`: Boolean indicating whether the operation was successful
- `message`: Human-readable message describing the outcome
- `errors`: List of field-specific errors if validation failed
- `admin`: The updated/created admin data (null if operation failed)

## Success States
- `success: true` with populated `admin`: Operation completed successfully
- `success: false` with `errors`: Validation or business rule failures

## Common Error Patterns
- Admin not found
- Invalid status change
- Insufficient permissions
- Self-suspension attempt

## Example Response (Success)
```json
{
  "data": {
    "suspendAdmin": {
      "success": true,
      "message": "Admin suspended successfully",
      "errors": null,
      "admin": {
        "id": "123",
        "firstName": "John",
        "lastName": "Doe",
        "status": "suspended"
      }
    }
  }
}
```

## Example Response (Error)
```json
{
  "data": {
    "suspendAdmin": {
      "success": false,
      "message": "Failed to suspend admin",
      "errors": [
        {
          "field": "adminId",
          "message": "Cannot suspend your own admin account"
        }
      ],
      "admin": null
    }
  }
}
```

Input for suspending an admin account.

## Fields
- `admin_id`: The unique identifier of the admin account to suspend

## Usage Notes
- Only active admins can suspend other admins
- Self-suspension is not permitted
- The suspended admin will immediately lose access to administrative functions
- All active sessions for the suspended admin will be invalidated

## Example
```graphql
mutation {
  suspendAdmin(input: {
    adminId: "123"
  }) {
    success
    message
    admin {
      id
      status
    }
  }
}
```

Response payload for KYC verification operations.

## Purpose
Provides a consistent response structure for all KYC component verification operations.
Used by admin users to approve individual KYC components for wallet-based verification.

## Fields
- `success`: Boolean indicating whether the verification operation was successful
- `message`: Human-readable message describing the outcome, includes smart detection of KYC completion
- `errors`: List of field-specific errors if validation failed
- `kyc_application`: The updated KYC application data with new verification status

## KYC Completion Detection
The message field includes intelligent detection of when all KYC components are approved:
- Standard verification: "Identity document verified successfully"
- All components approved: "Identity document verified successfully. All KYC components are now approved - application status updated to complete."

## Example Response (Standard Verification)
```json
{
  "data": {
    "verifyIdentityDocument": {
      "success": true,
      "message": "Identity document verified successfully",
      "errors": null,
      "kycApplication": {
        "id": "123",
        "status": "pending",
        "identityDocumentStatus": "approved"
      }
    }
  }
}
```

## Example Response (Final Component Approved)
```json
{
  "data": {
    "verifyBankInfo": {
      "success": true,
      "message": "Bank information verified successfully. All KYC components are now approved - application status updated to complete.",
      "errors": null,
      "kycApplication": {
        "id": "123",
        "status": "complete",
        "bankInfoStatus": "approved"
      }
    }
  }
}
```

